TASK 3: Customer Churn Data Preparation & EDA
🎯 Objective

To prepare telecom customer data for machine learning by performing:

Data cleaning
Feature engineering
Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
📂 Dataset
Dataset: Telco Customer Churn Dataset
Contains customer demographics, services, billing, and churn status.
🛠️ Technologies Used
Python 🐍
Pandas & NumPy
Seaborn & Matplotlib
Scikit-learn
⚙️ Project Workflow
1. Data Understanding
Loaded dataset using Pandas
Checked structure using .info() and .describe()
Identified missing and inconsistent values
2. Data Cleaning
Converted TotalCharges to numeric
Handled missing values (drop/impute)
Cleaned invalid entries
3. Feature Engineering
Created:
TenureGroup (customer lifecycle buckets)
AvgMonthlySpend
Converted Yes/No → 1/0
Applied one-hot encoding to categorical variables
4. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
Churn distribution using countplot
Contract vs churn analysis
Correlation heatmap
Monthly charges vs churn (boxplot)
📊 Key Insights
📉 Customers with month-to-month contracts churn the most
💰 Higher monthly charges lead to higher churn probability
⏳ Long-term customers are less likely to churn
🌐 Fiber optic users show higher churn rates
🧾 Paperless billing users churn slightly more
📁 Deliverables
✔️ Cleaned dataset (cleaned_churn_data.csv)
✔️ Jupyter Notebook (churn_analysis.ipynb)
✔️ Visualizations & insights
📗 TASK 4: Netflix Titles Dataset – EDA & Insights
